## Auto-Updates

The application checks for updates automatically.

### Publishing a Release

1. Update version in:
   - `package.json`
   - `src-tauri/Cargo.toml`
   - `src-tauri/tauri.conf.json`

2. Generate update signature:

```bash
# Generate keypair (once)
pnpm tauri signer generate -w ~/.tauri/myapp.key

# Sign the release bundle
pnpm tauri signer sign path/to/bundle
```

3. Create a GitHub Release with:
   - Version tag (e.g., `v1.0.0`)
   - Release bundles
   - `latest.json` manifest

### Update Manifest Format

```json
{
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "date": "2024-01-20T12:00:00Z",
  "platforms": {
    "darwin-x86_64": {
      "url": "https://github.com/user/repo/releases/download/v1.0.0/app.app.tar.gz",
      "signature": "signature_here"
    },
    "linux-x86_64": {
      "url": "https://github.com/user/repo/releases/download/v1.0.0/app.AppImage.tar.gz",
      "signature": "signature_here"
    },
    "windows-x86_64": {
      "url": "https://github.com/user/repo/releases/download/v1.0.0/app.msi.zip",
      "signature": "signature_here"
    }
  }
}
```
